<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550 E 1/119: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-24T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>33. Your 42, March 23, 1 p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d111fn11">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <p>… The President has stated that this Government will have no observer at
                            Genoa except yourself.</p>
                        <p>It is expected that you will keep this Government fully advised of what
                            goes on. While you are not to participate in the Conference, there is no
                            objection to your going to Genoa if you think it advisable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>